        body: 'A hex colour like <strong>#FF0000</strong> is three 2-digit hex values — one each for <strong>Red, Green and Blue</strong> light, from 00 to FF (0–255) per channel. Combine them and you can make any of <strong>16.7 million</strong> colours. Every front-end developer, UI designer and game artist works in these codes every day: <code>#FF0000</code> is pure red, <code>#000000</code> black, <code>#FFFFFF</code> white. Learn to read them and you can decode — or design — the exact colour of any pixel on screen.',
